{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"05159ba8-7a0e-402b-95b7-0bff37ba726c","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically on file save (hot reload).\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — only run tests whose fully qualified name contains that string. The `~` operator means \"contains\".\n\nYou can also filter by just the method name:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"Name=ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9e636c3d-758d-445f-be53-55fcbe2478e1","outputTokens":159,"requestId":"A037:21B4FC:19A121C:1D20809:69FE91F7"},"id":"c1140f01-36bb-447b-89c9-fa3a4e5ab3e5","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:46:35.991Z","parentId":"ebeb9f07-969f-4d2c-ad50-bba681b66ea2"}
